  "text": "We used human (residues 23 to 230; accession no. M13899) and hamster (Syrian golden hamster residues 23-231 and 90-231; accession no. K02234) recombinant prion protein (rPrP Sen ) that lacked a Histidine tag and were purified as described previously [CITATION_1] (Table 1) . Briefly, Escherichia coli (E. coli) carrying a pET41 vector (EMD, Billerica, MA, USA) with the PrP sequence was grown in Luria Broth (LB) media in the presence of Kanamycin (0.05 mg/mL) and Chloramphenicol (0.034 mg/mL) and protein expression was induced using Overnight Express Autoinduction System 1 (Novagen, Madison, WI, USA). Inclusion body preparations were isolated from~4 g of pelleted cells using the Bug Buster Master Mix (Novagen) protocol and stored at´20˝C.",
